/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_2782_ShortDesc", "A long, pole-like weapon with a sharpened end")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_2782_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> There were the knights, gleaming in richly wrought plate-armor, colored plumes waving above their burnished sallets. Their steeds, caparisoned with silk, lacquered leather and gold buckles, caracoled and curvetted as their riders put them through their paces. The early light struck glints from lance-points that rose like a forest above the array, their pennons flowing in the breeze.</> - Black Colossus

Lances are the shock weapon of the cavalry charge and they have the ability to break armies at the first engagement.
Despite being heavy and unwieldy, lances are always the first choice of weapon for cavalry (with the exception of the uniquely talented Hyrkanian horse archers).

True bravery is the ability to stand and face a cavalry charge - a bristling forest of lances being driven towards the line by hard-faced men on screaming horses.

Lances rarely survive first contact, breaking or splintering or being lodged through the chest of a foe. Most cavalry carry a secondary weapon into battle for this reason.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51715_ShortDesc", "A dubiously crafted stone pike")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51715_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Well, the folk of the city can't help us just now. And they might not, if they could. The people of the Black Countries are generally hostile to strangers. Probably stick us full of spears.</> - Red Nails

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

This pike is heavy on one end and difficult to aim. The scavenged materials used in its manufacture will deteriorate quickly, making this a thrust-and-bust weapon.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51711_ShortDesc", "A broad-headed iron pike")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51711_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">- Bracing their feet in the wallowing sea of blood whose crimson waves lapped about their ankles, the pikemen in the Pass mouth drove forward, crushing strongly against the milling ranks before them.</> - Black Colossus

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

Stygian hunters carry great broad-headed pikes to kill off the larger creatures that they encounter a commonly used but incredibly dangerous tactic is to goad the creature into charging while bracing the pike against the ground.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51931_ShortDesc", "An ornate pike made in the Stygian style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51931_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus

The Stygian armies are famed for using chariots into battle. This frees their hands to use either the bow or the spear to great effect.

The Stygian spear is heavy, two handed, and bronze tipped. Wielded with the momentum of a charging chariot it is devastating to infantry and cavalry alike.

Stygian hunters use the broad bladed spears to hunt lions and rhinoceros on the rocky plains around the Styx river.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51721_ShortDesc", "A heavy, three pronged spear")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51721_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Spears! he muttered. What a blasted fool I am not to have thought of that before! That shows what a pretty woman does to a man's mind.</> - Red Nails

Originally used for fishing along the Argossean coastline, the flamboyant gladiator Aros of Koth decided to adopt the trident as his signature weapon.

The extremely broad head of the weapon makes it top heavy and too thick to be used in a shield wall while the barbed prongs are prone to getting caught on armor and flesh. 

The trident is best used against large creatures where stopping power is more important than precision. Aros of Koth discovered this the hard way, earning renown and fortune for taking down the Beast Lizard of Messantia, but then being killed in a later encounter with a swarm of Darfari Cannibals.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51090_ShortDesc", "A pike forged from an ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51090_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

The ancient aura that clings to this pike fills any nearby with a distinct sense of dread. What unholy purpose were such weapons put to in the dim past? 

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51726_ShortDesc", "A spear with a hardened steel head")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51726_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The defile was blocked by a wild and terrible band of men who stood silent as images - ragged, shock-headed men with spears in their hands - hundreds of them. And up on the cliffs appeared other faces - thousands of faces - wild, gaunt, ferocious faces, marked by fire and steel and starvation.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this large spear baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

The Cimmerians make large, two-handed spears for maximum reach to hunt the most dangerous game animals. Such weapons are fine to have against more human opponents as well.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51101_ShortDesc", "A spear infused with venom")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51101_LongDesc", "This weapon has been infused with venom, making each cut envenom its victim.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51491_ShortDesc", "A pike of black glass")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51491_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this spear is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

The thick haft and weighted end mean that the pike must be wielded in two hands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81019_ShortDesc", "An extremely long and ancient polearm")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81019_LongDesc", "When this weapon was recovered from the body of the King Below, it had adjusted in size to fit human hands. Clearly magical in nature, the haft of the polearm is engraved with the runes that give it the name, Kingslayer.

The oddly shaped blade makes it more like a long-handled sword than a spear, yet it is balanced perfectly in the hands, as if eager to seek blood.

Whatever the story of this weapon, it will be an asset to those who wish to rule the Exiled Lands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51982_ShortDesc", "A vicious spear made in the Acheronian style")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51982_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus\n\nThis weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51514_ShortDesc", "A pike in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51514_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until someday, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

This War Spear is forged from blasphemous patterns obtained beneath the volcano from the last degenerate.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51515_ShortDesc", "A pike in a blasphemous ancient style")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92220_ShortDesc", "A pike crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92220_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time.

With superior reach the polearm is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the polearm is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51516_ShortDesc", "A pike in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51516_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until someday, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

This War Spear is forged from blasphemous patterns obtained beneath the volcano from the last degenerate.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51723_ShortDesc", "A spear with a head forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51723_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They met like a thunderclap. The Nemedian's lance, striking his foe's helmet, snapped bolts and rivets and tore off the casque, revealing the features of Pallantides. But the Aquilonian's lance-head crashed through shield and breast-plate to transfix the baron's heart.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This impossibly sharp spear has a head made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Spears are two-handed weapons with an ungainly tall wooden haft, but their reach is second to none.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51983_ShortDesc", "A vicious spear made in the Acheronian style")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51983_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">The horde had formed into a huge wedge, of which the tip was the Stygians and the body, the mailed asshuri, flanked by the nomads. In close formation, shields lifted, they rolled onward, while behind them a tall figure in a motionless chariot lifted wide-robed arms in grisly invocation.</> - Black Colossus\n\nThis weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51592_ShortDesc", "A long spear in the style of sunken Lemuria")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51592_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then the Cataclysm rocked the world. Atlantis and Lemuria sank, and the Pictish Islands were heaved up to form the mountain peaks of a new continent.</> - The Hyborian Age

With superior reach the pike is a common weapon on the battlefields of Hyboria. The most effective use of the pike is from behind the lines of battle, thrusting into the gaps in a shield wall.

The Lemurians were an island people, inhabiting an island chain off the eastern coast of the Thurian continent - until their kingdom sank beneath the waves. Their story took a brutal turn when they landed on the eastern coastline - and were promptly enslaved by the race of people who dwelt there.

What Lemurian artefacts are doing here is a mystery. Just like the Exiled Lands themselves.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4196_ShortDesc", "An improvised bar brawling weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4196_LongDesc", "A star metal shovel that has been outfitted with a sturdy grip and sharpened. It serves the dual function of both killing your opponent and using it to dig their grave.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51725_ShortDesc", "A spear with a head forged from mysterious star metal")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54001_ShortDesc", "A spear crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54001_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19609_ShortDesc", "A trident made in an ancient fashion")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19609_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Spears! he muttered. What a blasted fool I am not to have thought of that before! That shows what a pretty woman does to a man's mind.</> - Red Nails

Originally used for fishing along the Argossean coastline, the flamboyant gladiator Aros of Koth decided to adopt the trident as his signature weapon.

The extremely broad head of the weapon makes it top heavy and too thick to be used in a shield wall while the barbed prongs are prone to getting caught on armor and flesh. 

The trident is best used against large creatures where stopping power is more important than precision. Aros of Koth discovered this the hard way, earning renown and fortune for taking down the Beast Lizard of Messantia, but then being killed in a later encounter with a swarm of Darfari Cannibals.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51951_ShortDesc", "A pair of primitive stone-bladed knives")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51951_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan went with it, bruised, battered, invincible, hanging on like a bulldog to the hilt of his saber which he could not withdraw, tearing and ripping at the shuddering bulk with the poniard in his left hand, goring it to ribbons.</> - The Slithering Shadow

Sharpened stones serving as primitive daggers with limited ranged for fast, stabbing attacks.

Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51952_ShortDesc", "A pair of vicious short-bladed knives")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51952_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As he went he fingered the poniard he had captured - a murderous weapon with a broad, double-edged blade nineteen inches long.</> - Rogues in the House

Crafted of iron, these poniards taper quickly to a sharp point that can be used to puncture holes in armor and flesh.

A thin groove in the center of the poniard can be filled with venom harvested from various creatures of the Exiled Lands. Venoms cause excruciating pain before death but are particularly effective for incapacitating large animals.

This poniard does not bear any markers of origin.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51955_ShortDesc", "A pair of vicious short-bladed knives")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51955_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As he went he fingered the poniard he had captured - a murderous weapon with a broad, double-edged blade nineteen inches long.</> - Rogues in the House

This poniard does not bear any markers of origin.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51957_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers crafted from the eye of the Abysmal Remnant")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51957_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He saw and knew the ancient and evil serpent which swayed there, its wedge-shaped head, huge as that of a horse, as high as a tall man's head, and its palely gleaming barrel rippling out behind it. A forked tongue darted in and out, and the firelight glittered on bared fangs.</> - Beyond the Black River

As far as trophies go, these dagger are amongst the most bizarre. Made with the hypnotic eye of the Abysmal Remnant embedded in the blade, it has a fearsome aspect but does not seem to have any specific powers beyond that. 

Perhaps in time, certain powers will reveal themselves.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51956_ShortDesc", "A pair of vicious short-bladed knives")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51956_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As he went he fingered the poniard he had captured - a murderous weapon with a broad, double-edged blade nineteen inches long.</> - Rogues in the House

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51953_ShortDesc", "A pair of sharp-bladed off-hand daggers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51953_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Conan did not reply; he merely stood and glared at her with his burning eyes, testing the edge of his poniard with a callused thumb.</> - Rogues in the House

While all poniards are capable of fast stabbing attacks with their venom coated blades, the extra strength of a steel poniard means that it can also be used to parry the attacks of enemies.

Using a poniard to parry requires more skill than a shield, but if successful such a parry will leave the enemy open for counter attack. Poniards are the off-hand weapon of choice in Zingaran duels for exactly this reason.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51182_ShortDesc", "A pair of sharp-bladed off-hand daggers")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53997_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers crafted of exquisite bone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53997_LongDesc", "These daggers are old but very sharp. The bones that these daggers have been crafted from do not come from any of the animals that walks these lands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51942_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers forged from an ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51942_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?'</> - The God in the Bowl

These daggers are designed in imitation of a style long since faded into the mists of time.

Capable of cutting and dicing, slashing and slaying, daggers are for those who like to get in close and wreak havoc, then move to a safe distance while their foes bleed out.

Some warriors speak of the bloodlust that sweeps over them while using such weapons, an alien force that drives them to acts of great cruelty.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51959_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers with a hardened steel blade of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51959_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He grunted with satisfaction. The feel of the hilt cheered him and gave him a glow of confidence. Whatever webs of conspiracy were drawn about him, whatever trickery and treachery ensnared him, this knife was real. The great muscles of his right arm swelled in anticipation of murderous blows.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

These razor-sharp daggers are made of hardened steel and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
This weapon has limited ranged for its fast, stabbing attacks. Daggers and poniards are often coated in venom to increase their effectiveness.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51100_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers infused with venom")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51100_LongDesc", "This weapon has been infused with venom, making each cut envenom its victim.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51482_ShortDesc", "Short, sharp blades of black glass")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51482_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, these daggers are made of obsidian. They are brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nDaggers are a weapon used with passion by the untrained and with a cold dispassion by the trained. Unseasoned warriors consider swords the superior weapon - until they come across a master, twin blades flashing as they dash and dart within the reach of their enemies and disembowel them.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81020_ShortDesc", "An extremely sharp pair of ancient daggers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_81020_LongDesc", "When these weapon were recovered from the body of the King Below, they had adjusted in size to fit human hands. Clearly magical in nature, the handle of the dagger is engraved with the runes that give it the name, Kingslayer.\n\nWhatever the story of this weapon, it will be an asset to those who wish to rule the Exiled Lands.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4189_ShortDesc", "An improvised bar brawling weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4189_LongDesc", "The favored choice of many mean drunks, these shards can do serious damage when poked into the soft bits of your opponent.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51449_ShortDesc", "A pair of dual-bladed daggers")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51449_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">What is time to us? We stand outside. All things have happened. All things are happening.</> - Unknown\n\nThese daggers were crafted from the fangs of an enormous bear tamed by the nordheimers of Asghard.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51473_ShortDesc", "Claws that unleash the rage of the beast")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51473_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A man from the Tauran couldn't mistake the mark of a panther's claws. No. It's a forest devil summoned by Zogar Sag to carry out his revenge.</> - Beyond the Black River

With these equipped, the world takes on a red tinge. The power of Jhebbal Sag surges and the beast takes control.

With these equipped, new combinations of moves unlock and a warrior becomes a feral beast in combat.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51468_ShortDesc", "Claws that unleash the rage of the beast")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51468_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">A man from the Tauran couldn't mistake the mark of a panther's claws. No. It's a forest devil summoned by Zogar Sag to carry out his revenge.</> - Beyond the Black River

With these equipped, the world takes on a red tinge. The power of Jhebbal Sag surges and the beast takes control.

With these equipped, new combinations of moves unlock and a warrior becomes a feral beast in combat.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51450_ShortDesc", "A pair of dual-bladed daggers")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51450_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">What is time to us? We stand outside. All things have happened. All things are happening.</> - Unknown

These ceremonial daggers were taken from the corpse of Hoshun the Fang. The inscription on the daggers tell the story of his life - from growing up as a frail child in the streets of Sepermeru to growing up to become a family man, only to lose his children to the Reaping Storm, sacrificing his very soul to Set in order to keep his true love alive but ultimately losing her to a sandstorm. Hoshun was a good man. Was. Now, he is a pile of bones and dead flesh. All that is left are these daggers. Congratulations.

Light attacks with these daggers seem to take no effort, but heavy attacks seem to weary the wielder even more.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51393_ShortDesc", "A pair of daggers from the collection of the Priest King")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51393_LongDesc", "A religious item inscribed with holy runes, this relic was wrested from the undead hands of the Priest King\'s shade. These daggers draw venom from the veins of the wielder periodically.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19616_ShortDesc", "A dagger of ancient design")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19616_LongDesc", "This dagger was made to function similar to how a shark\'s bite works - it rips and shreds rather than cuts the flesh and causes tremendous wounds when doing so.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53712_ShortDesc", "A severed human arm")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53712_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan rose, still smiling, as if to reach into a near-by cooking pot; then quick as a cat he struck Aja a terrible blow with the heavy bone. The Bakalah war-chief slumped over, his skull crushed in, and instantly a frightful yell rent the skies as the Bamulas went into action like blood-mad panthers.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

Once, this limb belonged to a dangerous criminal, but now he can be considered 'armless. It looks like a left arm though, so he is all right. He can stump his enemies by pretending to surrender. Still, this entire incident has made him half as handy as he used to be. 
At least from now on you'll be well armed.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51301_ShortDesc", "A lump of stone on a stick")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51301_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> She saw clubs swing and descend with brutal force on kinky heads. Brands were kicked out of the fires, scattering sparks; hut-thatches smoldered and blazed up.</> - The Vale of Lost Women

A simple arrangement of sticks and stones equally useful for bashing in skulls and breaking bones.

Yoggites believe that rending the flesh of their sacrifices causes great offence to their god. Thus they favour blunt weapons when capturing sacrifices to be dragged screaming to their flesh pits. 

Though stone itself can survive for aeons, the bindings on any stone weapon have little chance of lasting through more than a single battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51186_ShortDesc", "A mace of unadorned iron")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51186_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Across the sea of heads and spears Conan's madmen saw Amalric's riders forging steadily through the rout, to the rise and fall of axes and maces, and a mad joy of victory exalted each man's heart and made his arm steel.</> - Black Colossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its place in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes. It bears no makers-mark and is made of untreated iron.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51087_ShortDesc", "A mace forged from an ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51087_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

This mace is designed in imitation of a style long since faded into the mists of time.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

Some warriors speak of the bloodlust that sweeps over them while using such weapons, an alien force that drives them to acts of great cruelty.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51078_ShortDesc", "A mace of hardened  steel")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51078_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">At their saddle-bows hung battle-axes or steel maces, and each man wore at his hip a long broadsword.</> - Black Collossus

A refinement of the primitive clubs swung by god-fearing savages in the wild places of the world, the mace has found its purpose in a world of armored figures.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

Cimmerian clans often forge weapons such as this for trade - theirs raids against the Vanir and Aesir of the north rarely require them to take down foes in heavy armor.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51485_ShortDesc", "A mace of black glass")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51485_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The three soldiers-men-at-arms wearing the emblem of the royal guards-rushed at the king, and one felled the squire with a blow of a mace.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this mace is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51526_ShortDesc", "A mace in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51526_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

This mace is forged from blasphemous patterns obtained beneath the volcano from the last degenerate.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51527_ShortDesc", "A mace in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51527_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51081_ShortDesc", "A mace forged from mysterious Star Metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51081_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The three soldiers-men-at-arms wearing the emblem of the royal guards-rushed at the king, and one felled the squire with a blow of a mace.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This mace is forged of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Capable of shattering bones through armor and crumpling helmets, the mace is a preferred weapon against heavily armored foes, bypassing the protection of their armor through sheer force.

This mace is exquisitely balanced, the metal forged with the perfect ratio of weight to power in mind. It gives off a satisfying whoosh as it passes through the air, as well.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4190_ShortDesc", "An improvised bar brawling weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4190_LongDesc", "Reinforced with a star metal core, this weapon may look improvised but in fact is nothing more than a solid metal stick made to look innocuous.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92221_ShortDesc", "Wrested from the defeated Thag")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92221_LongDesc", "Absence of light is not shadow; it is the end of hope.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51604_ShortDesc", "An inconspicuously primitive mace")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51604_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He sensed an inexorable driving fate behind all this. He could not escape. He was as much a captive as he had been in the pits of Belverus. But he was no son of the Orient to yield passively to what seemed inevitable. If he could not escape, he would at least take some of his foes into eternity with him.</> - Conan the Conqueror\n\nAt first glance, this mace seems very primitive. On closer inspection, however, a remarkable amount of care has been put into sharpening the jagged edges of it, enabling it to shred, rather than bash, through most armors.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51853_ShortDesc", "A tooth-edged sword of bone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51853_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With an awful shriek the witch sank down, writhing in convulsions, grasping at the naked blade as it was withdrawn, smoking and dripping.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nA mark of the Darfari wish to emulate more advanced cultures, this \"sword\" is more like a flat plank embedded with the teeth of various animals. It swings like a plank as well, so while it may not have the lethality of a well whetted blade, it will still leave a nasty mark on anything it managed to hit.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51850_ShortDesc", "A cudgel of Darfari make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51850_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He wondered how many poor devils had been bludgeoned in their sleep and dragged out of that room and down the road that ran through the shadowed palm groves to the roasting pit.</>  - Shadows in Zamboula

This sinister weapon is made of the bones of a human arm bound to a large fragment of stone. 

Bone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51833_ShortDesc", "A primitive axe, shaped by crude materials and bone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51833_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">With an awful shriek the witch sank down, writhing in convulsions, grasping at the naked blade as it was withdrawn, smoking and dripping.</> - A Witch Shall Be Born\n\nBone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51852_ShortDesc", "An unadorned axe of iron")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51852_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Traders had come, and priests of Mitra who walked with bare feet and empty hands, and died horribly, most of them; but soldiers had followed, men with axes in their hands and women and children in ox-drawn wains.</> - Beyond the Black River

This axe could have been crafted at any smithy the length of Hyboria.
Axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes. This axe does not bear any markers of origin.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51195_ShortDesc", "A vicious, double bladed iron axe")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51195_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Made of iron and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.")

/LongDesc:

The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

Made of iron and marked with the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan, this battle-axe is sharp, durable and capable of inflicting vicious wounds.

Battle-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51856_ShortDesc", "A macabre weapon of bone fused to rock")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51856_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> He wondered how many poor devils had been bludgeoned in their sleep and dragged out of that room and down the road that ran through the shadowed palm groves to the roasting pit.</>  - Shadows in Zamboula

This sinister weapon is made of the bones of a human arm bound to a large fragment of stone. 

Cannibalism is more than a perverted appetite to the men of Darfar: it is an integral element of their cult. This cudgel is one of the ritual objects of the Yoggite religion. It is used to bludgeon human prey so that they can be carried to the sacrifice pit unblemished.

Bone is a brittle substance that breaks easily under even a small amount of force. Anything made of bone will fall apart quickly.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51068_ShortDesc", "A great axe humming with frigid power")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51068_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">He did not wonder at the strangeness of it all, not even when two gigantic figures rose up to bar his way. The scales of their mail were white with hoar-frost; their helmets and their axes were covered with ice. Snow sprinkled their locks; in their beards were spikes of icicles; their eyes were cold as the lights that streamed above them.</> - The Frost-Giant\'s Daughter\n\nThe skalds of Nordheim sing storied songs of Ymir forging weapons out of ice and lightning. This axe, gelid as a tundra, gives proof to that legend with every thunder-crack blow.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51985_ShortDesc", "A vicious war-axe made in the Acheronian style")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51985_LongDesc", "This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50522_ShortDesc", "An ancient weapon found in the Unnamed City")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50522_LongDesc", "This spectral weapon, often employed by the wights and the undead, has been harnessed and bound to the realm of mortals and is now possible to wield by human hands. The weapon drains the soul from anyone its blade touches.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51521_ShortDesc", "A war-axe in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51521_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92216_ShortDesc", "A war-axe crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92216_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time. 

War-axes are a difficult weapon for inexperienced warriors, due to their smaller surface area and uneven balance. No other one-handed weapon shares their raw power, however, and they can wreak havoc on unarmored foes.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51603_ShortDesc", "An axe of Lemurian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51603_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then the Cataclysm rocked the world. Atlantis and Lemuria sank, and the Pictish Islands were heaved up to form the mountain peaks of a new continent.</> - The Hyborian Age

The Lemurians were an island people, inhabiting an island chain off the eastern coast of the Thurian continent - until their kingdom sank beneath the waves. Their story took a brutal turn when they landed on the eastern coastline - and were promptly enslaved by the race of people who dwelt there.

What Lemurian artefacts are doing here is a mystery. Just like the Exiled Lands themselves.")

Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4192_ShortDesc", "An improvised bar brawling weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4192_LongDesc", "A mad cook from Zingara once sharpened his spatula to a fine, flesh-tearing tool of destruction in order to guarantee total customer satisfaction.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92149_ShortDesc", "An improvised bar brawling weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92149_LongDesc", "For all weapons there is one end that is particularly unpleasant. Whomever broke this bottle made certain that the amount of unpleasant ends should vastly outnumber the amount of safe ones.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51085_ShortDesc", "An unholy relic, forged using with the black heart of the Kinscourge")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51085_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His one thought was to get out of the haunted chamber which had housed that beautiful, hideous, undead fiend for so many centuries.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This ancient axe pulses with blasphemous power.

This weapon is older than civilizations that are no longer remembered by the deepest histories. Its humming steel is full of bad memories. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51072_ShortDesc", "An unholy relic, forged using with the black heart of the Kinscourge")
/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54000_ShortDesc", "A war axe crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54000_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54006_ShortDesc", "Wrested from the undead hands of the Executioner")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54006_LongDesc", "A creature known only as the Executioner once wielded this. It is unknown how many eyes have glanced on the blade of this weapon before it has sunk its teeth into them but the indentions and grooves of the blade are caked with age-old blood.\n\nThis weapon will instantly destroy any opponent that has suffered significant enough damage.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92095_ShortDesc", "This War-Axe randomly causes additional damage")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92095_LongDesc", "Crafted by the legendary but mad blacksmith Jhus Thorse, this war-axe has the hallmarks of an incredibly well-made axe - in parts. Jhus was growing increasingly mad and forgetful with age. Some parts of the axe-blade has been sharpened to an incredible edge, while others have barely gotten any attention. This has the effect that when the axe hits a target it might - or might not - do extra damage depending on which part of the axe actually hits the target.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53713_ShortDesc", "A severed human leg")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53713_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan brained him with the beef bone, took his poniard and his keys, and made a leisurely departure.</> - Rogues in the House

This leg, severed from the corpse of an enemy, is bloodless and stiff. Carrying it around might not be a good way to make friends, but then again it might help to make a different kind of friend.
The important thing is that it can be used as a weapon. And beating someone to death with a limb is an itch that rarely gets scratched in civilized society.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51152_ShortDesc", "A crude two-handed stone hammer")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51152_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> His devotees died about that tomb in a crimson holocaust, but the barbarians could not burst the door, nor ever mar the structure by maul or fire.</> - Black Colossus

Crudely put together using a long branch and a large, heavy stone, this weapon will deteriorate quickly with use.

Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51213_ShortDesc", "Once a proud oar")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51213_LongDesc", "This oar has an enticing and familiar shape and design. It\'s a pity that it is broken but it will still serve the purpose of whacking someone over the head with it.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51151_ShortDesc", "A solid-iron Warhammer")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51151_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The wild Kushites rushed into the shambles, spearing the wounded, bursting the helmets of the knights with stones and iron hammers.</> - Black Colossus

Forged of iron, this Warhammer bears no markings to identify its maker.
Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Iron weapons last longer than stone weapons, but the iron found in the Exiled Lands is brittle and poor quality.")

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51162_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The wild Kushites rushed into the shambles, spearing the wounded, bursting the helmets of the knights with stones and iron hammers.</> - Black Colossus

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51154_ShortDesc", "A steel Warhammer")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51154_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The sheer weight of his shackles would have slain a lesser man with exhaustion. The locks that held band and chain were massive affairs that a sledge-hammer could hardly have dinted.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

Forged of steel, this Warhammer bears no markings to identify its maker.
Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

Steel weapons are the standard in the civilized kingdoms of Hyboria and savages find themselves at a distinct disadvantage when they find themselves pitting weapons of stone or wood against hardened steel.")

/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51155_ShortDesc", "A warhammer forged from an ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51155_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> 'This is a grisly thing,' shuddered the clerk. 'It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

Among the relics excavated from the ruins of the Exiled Lands are patterns for weapons that are familiar to blacksmiths. This Warhammer is one such weapon.

Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.

This hammer whispers to its bearer of the glory of strength. The sweetness of blood. The nobility of dying in battle. The succulence of marrow slurped raw from shattered bones. The flavor of eyeballs...")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51156_ShortDesc", "A hammer forged from hardened steel of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51156_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Limp and broken he sagged across the altar, his brains oozing from his crushed skull.</> - The Servants of Bit-Yakin

This fine hammer, shining with the blue of hardened steel, bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.
Such two-handed bludgeoning weapons are top heavy and designed to break the bones and brain armored and defensive opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51476_ShortDesc", "A massive hammer of black glass")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51476_LongDesc", "A sharp-edged, glassy stone. Not easily worked like iron or steel, obsidian can still be made into ridiculously brittle weapons.\n\nMauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51477_LongDesc", "A sharp-edged, glassy stone. Not easily worked like iron or steel, obsidian can still be made into ridiculously brittle weapons.\n\nMauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51523_ShortDesc", "A Warhammer in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51523_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

This Warhammer is forged from blasphemous patterns obtained beneath the volcano from the last degenerate.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51159_ShortDesc", "A hammer forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51159_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The people gave back as the body came hurtling down, to smash on the marble pave, spattering blood and brains, and lie crushed in its splintered armor, like a mangled beetle.</> - The Scarlet Citadel

This devastating hammer is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Such two-handed bludgeoning weapons are top heavy and designed to break the bones and brain armored and defensive opponents.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92218_ShortDesc", "A hammer crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92218_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time. 

Mauls and warhammers are slow to swing and leave their user vulnerable to counterattack, but when they connect they are brutally effective. Armored foes are particularly vulnerable to these massive blunt weapons which break bones, shatter skulls and crush spines.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4194_ShortDesc", "An improvised bar brawling weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4194_LongDesc", "Reinforced with a star metal core, this weapon may look improvised but in fact is nothing more than a solid metal stick made to look innocuous.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4193_ShortDesc", "Rigor mortis has set in a long time ago")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4193_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Conan brained him with the beef bone, took his poniard and his keys, and made a leisurely departure.</> - Rogues in the House

This leg, severed from the corpse of an enemy, is bloodless and stiff. Carrying it around might not be a good way to make friends, but then again it might help to make a different kind of friend.
The important thing is that it can be used as a weapon. And beating someone to death with a limb is an itch that rarely gets scratched in civilized society.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54002_ShortDesc", "A maul crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54002_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92235_ShortDesc", "Wrested from the defeated Thag")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92235_LongDesc", "Absence of light is not shadow; it is the end of hope.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4195_ShortDesc", "A wooden practice sword")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4195_LongDesc", "Practice makes perfect.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51801_ShortDesc", "A blunt, brittle sword")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51801_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> In the old free days, all I needed was a sharp sword and a straight path to my enemies. </> - The Phoenix on the Sword

This sword, created by binding a pair of sharpened stones to a hardwood branch, is unwieldy and unbalanced. More akin to a club than an actual bladed weapon, it will nevertheless be a capable tool for those trained in its use.

In the ice-locked lands north of Vanaheim and Asgard, adventurers tell of a tribe of man-apes who speak in the fashion of men and fashion rough weapons from stone and ice.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50495_ShortDesc", "A short bladed sword")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50495_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">...the narrow defile was packed and jammed with horses and men, the warriors crushed breast to breast, stabbing with shortened blades, slashing murderously when there was an instant's room to swing a sword.</> - People of the Black Circle

In primitive cultures, short swords are scoffed at as little more than knives. However, in the Hyborian cultures such as Aquilonia or Nemedia, where shield walls and cavalry charges have become a reality of combat, short swords are prized for their ability to thrust and stab in spaces where no longsword could ever be wielded.

A typical footsoldier in the armies of Aquilonia will carry a spear and a short sword along with their shield - and when the initial charge of battle is over and the slow roll of the meat grinder begins, it is short swords that decide the day.

Because they are smaller and weigh less than other weapons, short swords are also faster to use and consume less stamina than their larger counterparts.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_22030_ShortDesc", "An unholy weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_22030_LongDesc", "A spectral weapon, once wielded by an undead.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51811_ShortDesc", "A serviceable broadsword of iron")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51811_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans. This sword does not bear any markers of origin.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51814_ShortDesc", "An exceptional broadsword of iron")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51814_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans.

Due to the exceptional craftsmanship of this weapon, it will do more damage and take longer to break than other weapons of this type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51812_ShortDesc", "A sickle-sword used by the Stygian nobility")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51812_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loincloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood. With a terrible shout he hurled his broken hilt full into Conan's face, and leaping, seized the stallion's bridle.</> - Black Colossus

The favoured weapon of Stygian royalty, the khopesh is traditionally cast in bronze and hilted in pure ivory. With the development of stronger metals, the Stygian smiths began using iron and steel during their creation, and diluting out the bronze cast which made them pleasing to the nobility. 

Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51815_ShortDesc", "A flawless broadsword of iron")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51815_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The subtle tongue, the sophist guile, they fail when the broadswords sing;</> - The Road of Kings

A double bladed straight sword, the broadsword is popular among warriors and mercenaries from the Hyborian kingdoms. Equally suited to thrusting and slashing, a good broadsword can cut through mail shirts and cleave limbs and necks.

It is the hilt of a broadsword that represents its origin. It is easy to indentify the basket-hilted swords of Zingara and the heavy crosspiece hilts of the Hyperboreans.

This weapon is truly flawless and will do a lot more damage and take longer to break than other weapons of this type.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51818_ShortDesc", "A sickle-sword used by the Stygian nobility")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51818_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loincloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood. Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51958_ShortDesc", "A sword crafted from the eye of Abysmal Remnant")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51958_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">He saw and knew the ancient and evil serpent which swayed there, its wedge-shaped head, huge as that of a horse, as high as a tall man's head, and its palely gleaming barrel rippling out behind it. A forked tongue darted in and out, and the firelight glittered on bared fangs.</> - Beyond the Black River

Staring long enough into the eye of the Abysmal Remnant, embedded in this sword, fills the mind with bizarre images.

Once, the Priestking made a pact with a demon from the outer void to inhabit some formed flesh that he was crafting. This was to be a weapon, used in the war against the human city in the north.

The experiment failed, the creature was born limbless and the experiment was abandoned. An acolyte of the Priestking tossed it into the sewer system, to drown in The Dregs.

But the creature did not die, and the demon was not freed. It found a pool where it could excrete the acid that it needed to survive. And then it reached out with its mind, looking for food.

Over time, it grew and the rats and other vermin in the sewers were no long enough to sustain it...")

/LongDesc:

Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51822_ShortDesc", "A slashing weapon favoured by pirates")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51822_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> At this kind of fighting the freebooters of the sea were at their stoutest; their arrows and bolts tore holes in the charging horde, their cutlasses hewed the wild men from the palisades they strove to scale.</> - The Black Stranger

Favoured by sailors from the Western ocean to the Vilayet, the cutlass is a short, curved sword capable of hacking through ropes, canvas, wood, and flesh.

Forged of cheap iron, cutlasses are usually splotched with rust due to their time spent near salt water.  This cutlass does not bear any markers of origin.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51831_ShortDesc", "A common, thin bladed, double-edged sword")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51831_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.
The only description of a longsword that seems to be agreed upon is that they are double-bladed and straight. Beyond that they vary wildly from grooved blades to smooth blades, long hilts to short hilts, one-handed and two-handed variations.
This example is plain, straight and intended to be wielded in a single hand.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51836_ShortDesc", "A common, thin bladed, double-edged sword")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51836_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51821_ShortDesc", "A curved sword with a single sharp edge")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51821_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A man on a giant horse whirled, slashed and smote apparently at thin air, and from another direction swept a wild horde of riders, their curved swords flashing in the moonlight.</> - Drums in Tombalku

Straddling the line between the traditional khopesh of Stygia and broadsword favoured in the northern kingdoms, the falcata is forward curved blade with a single edge on the concave side.

The distinctive hooked hilt helps to prevent the weapon from jarring free of the hands during battle. There is much dispute about the origin of the weapon, considering its similarity to the Argossean kopis and the Stygian khopesh.  This falcata bears no marking which would betray its origin.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51947_ShortDesc", "A sword with an eye attached to it")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51947_LongDesc", "This sword was pillaged from the corpse of the Man on the Wall. It is a curious item that feels warm to the touch.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51841_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel sword of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51841_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Stand aside, girl,' he mumbled. 'Now is the feasting of swords.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk
Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this broadsword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51817_ShortDesc", "A Khopesh stamped with the symbol of the serpent")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51817_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The common men of Stygia were not allowed to wear swords, and the mantle was not voluminous enough to hide the Cimmerian's long blade, but Conan buckled to his hip a Ghanta knife, a weapon borne by the fierce desert men who dwelt to the south of the Stygians, a broad, heavy, slightly curved blade of fine steel, edged like a razor and long enough to dismember a man.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

It is forbidden in the kingdom of Stygia for the common man to bear a sword, but the khopesh, particularly one that has taken part in the bloody rituals of Set, is allowed.

This khopesh appears to be made of steel, yet it is tinted the bronze color that Stygian ceremonial garb requires. The symbol engraved on the blade is the symbol of Set, the sacred serpent. Blades such as these are passed among the priesthood and given to those who show particular fervor when participating in the rites of blood.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92167_ShortDesc", "An incredibly sharp Cutlass")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92167_LongDesc", "Named the \'Seasalt Cutlass\' by virtue of it\'s notably sharp sting when forcefully inserted into people\'s mouth, this weapon has coined the term \'Salting the wound\' by the pirates of the Black Cove.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19599_ShortDesc", "A strange sword with a hook at the end")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19599_LongDesc", "To a trained professional, this sword would work both as a tool for hooking fish and as a weapon.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51813_ShortDesc", "An ancient khopesh marked in strange runes")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51813_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> You shall go down the dark road to Acheron, which is the road of silence and the night. The dark empire, unreborn, shall remain a legend and a black memory.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This khopesh, made from an ancient design, seems to suck away the warmth and daylight. A relic of the past, the shape of it calls up shadow-haunted memories of ape-gods squatting on shattered altars.

It whispers ceaselessly to its bearer and slowly, inevitably, tears their sanity apart.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51816_ShortDesc", "A broadsword carved with the symbol of the phoenix")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51816_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And as he stood, bewildered at the strangeness of his dream, he realized that he was gripping his sword in his hand. And his hair prickled at the nape of his neck, for on the broad blade was carven a symbol- the outline of a phoenix.</> - The Phoenix on the Sword

When the world was young, there was a great sage known as Epimetreus. Little is known of the shadowy past in which he fought with Set, the arch-demon, but it is known that for all the days of his life he strove against the worshippers, votaries and acolytes of the Old Serpent.

It is rumored that in times of need the ghost of Epimetreus flies on unseen wings to aid the kingdom of Aquilonia, and that the symbol of the phoenix belongs to the sage as much as it does to Mitra.

In any case, there is nothing to distinguish this sword from any other - save the glowing symbol of the phoenix carved into the blade.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51843_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel sword of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51843_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'Stand aside, girl,' he mumbled. 'Now is the feasting of swords.'</> - Xuthal of the Dusk
Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this broadsword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51097_ShortDesc", "A sword infused with venom")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51097_LongDesc", "This weapon has been infused with venom, making each cut envenom its victim.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51494_ShortDesc", "A sword of black glass")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51494_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this sword is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nSwords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51073_ShortDesc", "An unholy weapon")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51073_LongDesc", "A spectral weapon, once wielded by an undead.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50499_ShortDesc", "A short bladed sword")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50499_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">...the narrow defile was packed and jammed with horses and men, the warriors crushed breast to breast, stabbing with shortened blades, slashing murderously when there was an instant's room to swing a sword.</> - People of the Black Circle

In primitive cultures, short swords are scoffed at as little more than knives. However, in the Hyborian cultures such as Aquilonia or Nemedia, where shield walls and cavalry charges have become a reality of combat, short swords are prized for their ability to thrust and stab in spaces where no longsword could ever be wielded.

A typical footsoldier in the armies of Aquilonia will carry a spear and a short sword along with their shield - and when the initial charge of battle is over and the slow roll of the meat grinder begins, it is short swords that decide the day.

Because they are smaller and weigh less than other weapons, short swords are also faster to use and consume less stamina than their larger counterparts.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50521_ShortDesc", "An ancient weapon found in the Unnamed City")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50521_LongDesc", "This spectral weapon, often employed by the wights and the undead, has been harnessed and bound to the realm of mortals and is now possible to wield by human hands. The weapon drains the soul from anyone its blade touches.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51496_ShortDesc", "A sword of black glass")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51496_LongDesc", "Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this sword is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.\n\nSwords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51979_ShortDesc", "A vicious sword made in the Acheronian style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51979_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> They stopped short. Conan faced them, not a naked man roused mazed and unarmed out of deep sleep to be butchered like a sheep, but a barbarian wide-awake and at bay, partly armored, and with his long sword in his hand.</>
The Phoenix on the Sword

Longsword has become a catch-all phrase for the mongrel swords of a thousand different makes that don't align easily with one simple classification.

This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51517_ShortDesc", "A sword in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51517_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

This sword is forged from blasphemous patterns obtained beneath the volcano from the last degenerate.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51069_ShortDesc", "A sword forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51069_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'This day you become knights!' he laughed fiercely, pointing with his dripping sword towards the hillmen horses, herded nearby. 'Mount and follow me to hell!'</> - Black Colossus

This impossibly sharp sword is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51070_ShortDesc", "A sword forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
