/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51593_ShortDesc", "A sword in the style of sunken Lemuria")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51593_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Then the Cataclysm rocked the world. Atlantis and Lemuria sank, and the Pictish Islands were heaved up to form the mountain peaks of a new continent.</> - The Hyborian Age

Swords are straight-bladed, one-handed weapons, both fast and reliable.

The Lemurians were an island people, inhabiting an island chain off the eastern coast of the Thurian continent - until their kingdom sank beneath the waves. Their story took a brutal turn when they landed on the eastern coastline - and were promptly enslaved by the race of people who dwelt there.

What Lemurian artefacts are doing here is a mystery. Just like the Exiled Lands themselves.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51975_ShortDesc", "A sword fashioned out of pure black ice")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51975_LongDesc", "The blade of this weapon is warm to the touch, despite it being made out of pure black ice. Beneath the shimmering surface of the blade, shadows seem to move.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92237_ShortDesc", "A sword crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92237_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19607_ShortDesc", "A strange sword with a hook at the end")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19607_LongDesc", "To a trained professional, this sword would work both as a tool for hooking fish and as a weapon.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51950_ShortDesc", "A sword fashioned out of pure black ice and infused with blood")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51950_LongDesc", "Infused with the blood of thousands of victims, this blade has been blessed by Tsathoggua.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54005_ShortDesc", "A sword crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54005_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54007_ShortDesc", "Wrested from the undead hands of the Executioner")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_54007_LongDesc", "A creature known only as the Executioner once wielded this. It is unknown how many eyes have glanced on the blade of this weapon before it has sunk its teeth into them but the indentions and grooves of the blade are caked with age-old blood.\n\nThis weapon will instantly destroy any opponent that has suffered significant enough damage.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51088_ShortDesc", "A sword forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51088_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'This day you become knights!\' he laughed fiercely, pointing with his dripping sword towards the hillmen horses, herded nearby. \'Mount and follow me to hell!\'</> - Black Colossus\n\nThis impossibly sharp sword is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman. This particular sword was wrested from one of the Broodguards at the heart of the Volcano and has been sharpened until it could cut the very air itself.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51086_ShortDesc", "An ancient sword, haunted and grim")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51086_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His one thought was to get out of the haunted chamber which had housed that beautiful, hideous, undead fiend for so many centuries.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This ancient sword pulses with blasphemous power.

This weapon is older than civilizations that are no longer remembered by the deepest histories. Its humming steel is full of bad memories. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51810_ShortDesc", "A sickle-sword used by the Stygian nobility")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51810_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> It was prince Kutamun, naked but for a loincloth, his harness hacked away, his crested helmet dented, his limbs splashed with blood. With a terrible shout he hurled his broken hilt full into Conan's face, and leaping, seized the stallion's bridle.</> - Black Colossus

The favoured weapon of Stygian royalty, the khopesh is traditionally cast in bronze and hilted in pure ivory. With the development of stronger metals, the Stygian smiths began using iron and steel during their creation, and diluting out the bronze cast which made them pleasing to the nobility. 

Interestingly, this weapon has more in common with an axe than a sword and is best used for hacking and chopping rather than slicing and dicing.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4197_ShortDesc", "A wooden practice sword")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_4197_LongDesc", "Practice makes perfect.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51043_ShortDesc", "A  crude two-handed sword made out of sharpened stone")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51043_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> His devotees died about that tomb in a crimson holocaust, but the barbarians could not burst the door, nor ever mar the structure by maul or fire.</> - Black Colossus

Crudely put together using a long branch and a large, heavy stone, this weapon will deteriorate quickly with use.

This sword is a straight-bladed, two-handed weapons, as heavy as it is powerful.

Even the most primitive weapons can mean the difference between life and death for an Exile.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51091_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of Yamatai design")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51091_LongDesc", "The people of Yamatai trade regularly along the eastern coastline of the Thurian continent - and their dhows can be seen docked from Vendhya and Kambuja to Paikang in Khitai. They have access to purer forms of metal on their volcanic islands than many of the cultures on the main continent. \n\nThey have developed a process called \'steel folding\' that allows them to create very strong, sharp blades with a high amount of metal purity. This type of smithing is a closely guarded secret and would not be willingly taught to strangers.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51092_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of Yamatai design")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51092_LongDesc", "The people of Yamatai trade regularly along the eastern coastline of the Thurian continent - and their dhows can be seen docked from Vendhya and Kambuja to Paikang in Khitai. /ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50509_ShortDesc", "An ancient weapon found in the Unnamed City")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50509_LongDesc", "A finely crafted, almost paper-thin blade with tremendous cutting power that would negate almost any armor. This cutting power is not without drawback, however, as the damage of the blade is also reduced.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51093_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of Yamatai design")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51044_ShortDesc", "A two-handed Iron sword")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51044_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">\'I pay my way with steel!\' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast\n\nGreat swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51061_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel, two-handed sword of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51061_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the blade of this massive sword, baring the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51098_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword infused with venom")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51098_LongDesc", "This weapon has been infused with venom, making each cut envenom its victim.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51479_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of black glass")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51479_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun. 'By Crom, man, if you don't get under way, I'll drench this galley in the blood of its crew!'</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this sword is made of obsidian. It is brittle, but the sharp facets of the black glass will cause additional damage to opponents.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51094_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of Yamatai design")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51094_LongDesc", "The people of Yamatai trade regularly along the eastern coastline of the Thurian continent - and their dhows can be seen docked from Vendhya and Kambuja to Paikang in Khitai. They have access to purer forms of metal on their volcanic islands than many of the cultures on the main continent. \n\nThey have developed a process called \'steel folding\' that allows them to create very strong, sharp blades with a high amount of metal purity. This type of smithing is a closely guarded secret and would not be willingly taught to strangers.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51599_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword of Acheronian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51599_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">'I pay my way with steel!' roared the man in armor, brandishing the great sword that glittered bluely in the sun.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

This weapon is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51063_ShortDesc", "A two-handed sword forged from mysterious star metal")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51063_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Something came writhing up the steps, something that slithered and rustled and brought a chill in the air with it. Conan lashed down with his great sword and felt the blade shear through something that might have been flesh and bone, and cut deep into the stair beneath.</> - Red Nails

This impossibly sharp great sword is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Great swords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92217_ShortDesc", "A great-sword crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92217_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time.

Greatswords are faster than many other two-handed weapons, and their great reach makes them ideal for fending off groups of opponents.")

/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51605_ShortDesc", "This blade seems impossibly black")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51605_LongDesc", "Mastercrafted in the eastern kingdoms, the metal used to forge blade with has been folded several million times. It is the epitome of craftsmanship, infused with the very soul of its creator.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53999_ShortDesc", "A sword crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53999_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51075_ShortDesc", "An ancient sword, haunted and grim")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51075_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">His one thought was to get out of the haunted chamber which had housed that beautiful, hideous, undead fiend for so many centuries.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This ancient sword pulses with blasphemous power.

This weapon is older than civilizations that are no longer remembered by the deepest histories. Its humming steel is full of bad memories. ")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51600_ShortDesc", "A rudimentary shield of loosely bound branches")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51600_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Presently the intention of the pirates became apparent to all, as a group of some thirty men advanced, pushing before them a great shield made out of the planks from the boats, and the timbers of the boat-house itself.</> - The Black Stranger

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

This shield is a primitive bundle of branches, strapped together with rudimentary twine made from plant fibres. It will shatter under sustained blows, but it might be the difference between life and death.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51601_ShortDesc", "A shield lashed together from the bones of the dead")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51601_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Wildly driven spears and knives glanced from his helmet or the shield on his left arm, while his broadsword cleft flesh and bone, split skulls, scattered brains and spilled entrails into the bloody dust.</> - The Snout in the Dark

Bones lashed to a wooden frame make for an intimidating defensive wall. Unfortunately, the brittle nature of bone means that intimidation is the strongest element of this shield. A few blows and it will shatter and leave the wielder vulnerable.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Darfari cannibals often craft this type of shield from the leftover bones in their sacrifice pits. The smell of charred flesh still clings to the bones.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51624_ShortDesc", "An ornate Stygian shield")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51624_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.'</> - Black Colossus

This ornamental shield, usually used by Stygian soldiers in ceremonial parade, is strong enough to offer formidable protection against attacks. The ridges and ornamentations provide an advantage in battle, catching the blades of the enemy as they slide along the rim while allowing full visibility of the enemy.

Ceremonial versions of this shield are usually wrought in brass and gold, but the more practical versions use tinted iron and steel.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51500_ShortDesc", "A shield made from shaleback shell")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51500_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

The shell of the shaleback provides them with excellent protection against the elements and predators of the Exiled Lands. It is strong and durable, though it tends to chip and flake in the midst of battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51501_ShortDesc", "A shield made from shaleback shell")
/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51602_ShortDesc", "A sturdy targe of wooden planks reinforced with iron")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51602_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Shields crashed against shields, and between them spears drove in and blood spurted.</> - Black Colossus

A round shield, reinforced with metal around the rim and leather straps for ease of holding. It is not uncommon to cover the front of the targe with a sheet of leather or hide and decorate it with patterns.

The targe is a shield designed for attack as much as defence. A well placed strike with the shield can stagger an enemy and leave them open to attacks from a weapon in the main hand.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51611_ShortDesc", "A targe covered by iron shielding")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51611_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> In ecstasy warriors clashed their notched swords on their riven shields, and the people of the town, ragged beggars and rich merchants, harlots in red kirtles and dames in silks and satins, fell to their knees and cried out for joy to Mitra, tears of gratitude streaming down their faces. </> - The Scarlet Citadel

Strengthened with iron, this targe sacrifices some of its manoeuvrability for additional durability. The knobs on the front of the shield are designed to notch the weapons and claws of foes. 

The rivets and design work do not point to a particular cultural tradition, but rather reflect the experimental nature of smith work in the Exiled Lands.

The targe is a shield designed for attack as much as defence. A well placed strike with the shield can stagger an enemy and leave them open to attacks from a weapon in the main hand.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51497_ShortDesc", "A shield of hardened carapace")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51497_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

This shield is crafted from the hardened carapace of one of the insectoid creatures that roams the Exiled Lands. It is strong and durable - but not as effective as a shield made of metal.")

/LongDesc:

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51621_ShortDesc", "A heater shield of beaten steel")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51621_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> Black Collossus

Usable by both infantry and cavalry, the heater shield is known for its unique shape and large area of protection.

As a defensive material, there is very little than can match the quality of steel. The additional weight is worth the extra protection.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51626_ShortDesc", "A heater shield of beaten steel")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51626_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> - Black Colossus

As a defensive material, there is very little than can match the quality of steel. The additional weight is worth the extra protection.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51607_ShortDesc", "A shield made from the hardened carapace of the Scorpion Queen")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51607_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

This shield is crafted from the hardened carapace of the Scorpion Queen. It is strong and extremely durable and offers a bonus to armor while wielded.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51622_ShortDesc", "A large shield with a slot for a lantern")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51622_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Arus stood in a vast corridor, lighted by huge candles in niches along the walls. These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Shields traditionally serve a single purpose defense. The lantern shield attempts to broaden that definition, however, by providing adventurers with a series of options for both attack and defense.

Developed in Argos, this small shield was originally designed to protect the watchmen of that city as they went about their nightly rounds, providing them with a handy light source for the darkest alleyways and corners of the city. However, the wily gladiators of Messantian fighting pits soon saw that the focused light of the lanterns mounted on the shield could be used to bedazzle and confuse their foes especially in the darkness.

Lantern shields come in many designs, from buckler shapes with jutting sword breakers and attached gauntlets, to simply large shield with an enclosure for holding the lantern that gives the shield its name.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51627_ShortDesc", "A heater shield of beaten steel")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51627_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> - Black Colossus

Usable by both infantry and cavalry, the heater shield is known for its unique shape and large area of protection.

As a defensive material, there is very little than can match the quality of steel. The additional weight is worth the extra protection.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51625_ShortDesc", "A ceremonial shield dedicated to Set")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51625_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

Among the rituals of the cult of Set, is the ability to render special properties into base metals. In particular, gold is much favored by the priests of Set to be used in the creation of these divine shields, which they claim will offer the blessings of Set.

Some have pointed out that the process which hardens the gold darkens it almost to the color of bronze, and that the specialized priests who perform the process often move on quickly to new cities and villages. But not too loudly. That would be blasphemous.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51628_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel shield of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51628_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Through a whistling cloud of arrows they plowed to break like a thundering wave on the bristling wall of spears and shields.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

This hardened steel shield bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second best blow is the one that you block.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for armor of unusually strong aegis.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51629_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel shield of Cimmerian make")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51629_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Through a whistling cloud of arrows they plowed to break like a thundering wave on the bristling wall of spears and shields.</> - The Hour of the Dragon

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51623_ShortDesc", "A whispering shield forged from an ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51623_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> I am cursed. A fiend from the abysses has set his mark upon me. Night after night he lurks in the shadows, whispering awful secrets to me.</> - Black Colossus

This shield was created from designs looted in the unnamed city ruins within the Exiled Lands. The design of the shield is intricate, with a serpentlike design that is both repellent and fascinating when examined.
This shield is heavy but the solid construction offers additional protection against repeated blows. 

When equipped, this shield seems to whisper to its bearer in the long forgotten language of the Giant-Kings. This constant distraction drains the willpower of the user, but those who master it may uncover hidden strengths.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51488_ShortDesc", "A shield of black glass")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51488_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> - Black Colossus

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this shield is made of obsidian. Nobody knows what the purpose of a glass shield is, but perhaps the black glass is strengthened when formed into such a lattice.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51988_ShortDesc", "A shield made from an Acheronian design")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51988_LongDesc", "Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.\n\nThis shield is forged in the style of ancient Acheron, a kingdom of sorcerers that dominated the northern kingdoms over three thousand years ago. Scholars have noted that the Acheronian style bears a striking similarity to that of the mysterious pre-human race that once ruled what is modern-day Stygia.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51508_ShortDesc", "A shield in a blasphemous ancient style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51508_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">And at last mankind conquered, so long ago that naught but dim legends come to us through the ages. The snake-people were the last to go, yet at last men conquered even them and drove them forth into the waste lands of the world, there to mate with true snakes until some day, say the sages, the horrid breed shall vanish utterly.</> - The Shadow Kingdom

The snake-people were thought to be gone. First defeated in the war with first man at the dawn of time, then purged again by King Kull of Valusia.

But here, in this bizarre, mysterious piece of the world, they found succor with the Giant-kings. Perhaps the city in the volcano was ancient before even the Giant-kings lived in this land. But either way, the degenerate remnant remains.

This shield is forged from blasphemous patterns obtained beneath the volcano from the last degenerate.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51490_ShortDesc", "A shield of black glass")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51490_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The Stygians had discarded their bows; helmeted heads bent to the blast, dark eyes glaring over the rims of their shields, they came on in an inexorable surge, striding over their fallen comrades.</> - Black Colossus

Forged in the depths of the Volcano that looms over the Exiled Lands, this shield is made of obsidian. Nobody knows what the purpose of a glass shield is, but perhaps the black glass is strengthened when formed into such a lattice.

Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51834_ShortDesc", "A shield made from old tusks")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51834_LongDesc", "Made from tusks as opposed to bone, this shield is stronger than it\'s more basic cousin.")

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51632_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">These walls were hung with black velvet tapestries, and between the tapestries hung shields and crossed weapons of fantastic make.</> - The God in the Bowl

/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51991_LongDesc", "Most warriors prefer to carry a shield into battle if there is one available. The best blow is the one that misses, but the second-best blow is the one that you block.

Through the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.

The sad reality of dragons was that they could not fly, they did not breathe fire or acid, and they were not particularly intelligent. They were simply gigantic predators that lived centuries ago.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19608_ShortDesc", "An old steering wheel from a galleon remade into a shield")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_19608_LongDesc", "This shield is made from sturdy wood, and although it might be waterlogged, is still robust enough to offer protection from attacks. However, it grants no additional armor and smells faintly of fish.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50489_ShortDesc", "A wickedly shaped two-handed axe")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50489_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">The giants answered with roars like the grinding of icebergs on a frozen shore and heaved up their shining axes as the maddened Cimmerian hurled himself upon them.</> - The Frost Giant's Daughter

A weapon that combines the razor edge of the Great Sword with the momentum and weight of the Warhammer, the Great Axe is a vehicle of savagery and slaughter.

The brutish strength required to swing the weapon with any degree of accuracy means that the weapon is rarely wielded by commoners. More often it is reserved for the ceremonial guards of kings where it is used to convey power and presence.
Tsotha-lanti, a Kothian wizard, is known to keep a guard of slaves - chosen for their intimidating height - equipped with these long handled axes.

In battle, a warrior who can control the weapon can create a whirlwind of steel around themselves, forcing their foes to stay at a distance or be torn to shreds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92222_ShortDesc", "Wrested from the defeated Thag")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92222_LongDesc", "Absence of light is not shadow; it is the end of hope.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51594_ShortDesc", "A dubiously crafted stone spear")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51594_LongDesc", "The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it\'s ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.\n\nIn addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51911_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear that can be jabbed or thrown")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51911_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> As they swept past the black mouth of a gorge that opened into the Pass, a javelin swished through the air and thudded home behind the stallion's straining shoulder.</> - The People of the Black Circle

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Light weight enough to be wielded with a shield, the javelin is a common front line weapon in battles. 

Push, stab, push, stab is a motto of infantry the world over.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51922_ShortDesc", "A short spear of the Darfari style")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51922_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Black men came up the river in long boats with skulls grinning on the prows, or stole stooping through the trees, spear in hand.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Adorned with feathers and tipped with flint, this short spear represents the pinnacle of Darfari weapons.

The Darfari use these spears for hunting game, first pinning their prey with well-aimed throws and then harassing their prey with swift, sharp stabs.

The feathers on the shaft are taken from the ferocious, but colourful, elephant birds that roam the grasslands on the very edges of Darfar.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51084_ShortDesc", "One-handed short spear of ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51084_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It's too ancient to be holy. Who ever saw metal like it in a sane world?</> - The God in the Bowl

The javelin is one of the most versatile weapons of the Hyborian age. Of course, this javelin is not of the Hyborian Age - it's ancient design is based upon writings from thousands of years ago.

In addition, the javelin is light enough to be thrown with some degree of accuracy. Enemies fleeing a battle are almost always surprised to find three feet of spear jutting from between their shoulder blades.

When equipped, this javelin seems to whisper to its bearer in the long forgotten language of the Giant-Kings. This constant distraction drains the willpower of the user, but those who master it may uncover hidden strengths.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_50516_ShortDesc", "An ancient weapon found in the Unnamed City")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53736_ShortDesc", "A short spear crafted of exquisite dragonbone")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53736_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51946_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51946_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51203_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails\n\nHeld in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51932_ShortDesc", "A hardened steel axe balanced for throwing")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51932_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">It wheeled at the thud of her soft boots on the floor, but even as it turned, her keen blade lashed down, and a fierce exultation swept her as she felt the edge cleave solid flesh and mortal bone.</> - Red Nails

Hardened steel, finely wrought, forms the head of this throwing axe and bears the swirling markings of a Cimmerian clan.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Cimmerians may be called savages and barbarians, but their understanding of metal smithing is relatively advanced. They know the riddle of steel, how to harden it for greater durability and vicious wounds.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51938_ShortDesc", "An axe forged from star metal and balanced for throwing")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51938_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">I am a queen by fire and steel and slaughter...</> - Queen of the Black Coast

This impossibly sharp throwing axe is made of legendary star metal, the work of a master craftsman.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.

Star metal is rare, smelted from ore that falls from the heavens. Weapons made from such material are preternaturally powerful.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53735_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_53735_LongDesc", "<span style=\"italic\">And their magicians made a terrible magic to guard the city; for by their necromantic arts they re-created the dragons which had once dwelt in this lost land, and whose monstrous bones they found in the forest. Those bones they clothed in flesh and life, and the living beasts walked the earth as they walked it when time was young.</> - Red Nails\n\nThrough the long passage of eons, rumors of dragons have always been passed down from generation to generation, and the legacy of these fearsome creatures grows with each telling.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51944_ShortDesc", "A light axe balanced for throwing")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51944_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> And it was suspicious. It lifted its head, its eyes glowing like balls of fire, and growled low in its throat. And at that instant Conan hurled the axe. </> - Beyond the Black River

The Vanir raiders who plague the lands of the Cimmerians and Aesir often carry these light axes on their belts during their raids.

Held in the off-hand, these axes can be used for hacking at enemy shields and, in an emergency, hurled at their faces.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51408_ShortDesc", "A light composite bow crafted of branches and thick leather")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51408_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Kerim Shah had unslung the powerful Turanian bow that killed at five hundred paces, and the Irakzai looked to their own lighter and less lethal bows.</> - The People of the Black Circle

This bow is made in the Hyrkanian style, using different materials to strengthen different areas of the bow and allowing it to be shorter than a longbow. For Hyrkanians, who spend most of their lives shooting from horseback, this is a necessity.

Hyrkanians are widely considered the best archers in the world, raised to the hunt and the art of shooting from horseback. Their bows, however, are not as well made as those of the Shemites, who have spent centuries perfecting the art.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92094_ShortDesc", "This bow has a demonic entity bound to it")
/LongDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92094_LongDesc", "It is unknown as to which specific demonic entity is bound to this bow, but whichever it is, it hungers for death. A pity, then, that the entity this demon possessed was merely a goat. Otherwise, this weapon could have been quite formidable.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51406_ShortDesc", "A bow forged from an ancient design")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51406_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> Springing to his feet, he bent his bow powerfully and drove his last shaft point blank at a great hairy shape that soared up at his throat. The arrow was a flying beam of moonlight that flashed onward with but a blur in its course, but the were-beast plunged convulsively in midair and crashed headlong, shot through and through.</> - Queen of the Black Coast

Created based on an ancient design found in the Exiled Lands, this bow seems to confuse the eye with its odd, alien curves.

In the thrum of the bowstring, it whispers of gibbering terrors screeching beneath a blood-red moon and the terrified screams of those who flee the merciless hunt.

One who holds this bow too long risks being drawn into its miasma of madness.")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51589_ShortDesc", "A bow reinforced with Hardened Steel")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_51589_LongDesc", "<span style="italic"> A long bow and a strong bow, and let the sky grow dark! The cord to the nock, the shaft to the ear, and the king of Koth for a mark!</>
Song of the Bossonian Archers.

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.

This bow will be able to bring down both human and non-human foes, but it relies heavily on the skill of the wielder.
")

/ShortDesc: NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92236_ShortDesc", "A composite bow crafted in the lost art of a dead civilization")
/LongDesc:
NSLOCTEXT("", "ItemTable_92236_LongDesc", "<span style="italic">Its composition was something like copper, but much harder, and it was carved with hieroglyphics, like those found on the more ancient menhirs in southern Stygia.</> - The God in the Bowl

Historians link the rise and eventual fall of the Khari empire to its dominion over the slave trade. In fact, it's believed the Khari gained their reputation as master crafters through the careful theft and assimilation of knowledge held by those they enslaved.

When the inevitable occurred and slave turned against master, Khari survivors fled west to the desert where they encountered the last remaining vestiges of the serpent people. As devout worshippers of Set, the Khari venerated the serpent folk as living scions of their beloved reptile God and laid the foundations for the kingdom that would later be known as Stygia. What finally befell the Khari and their scaled patrons is lost to time. 

In trained hands, bows are lethal weapons that can bring down a foe from afar. A large part of the versatility of the bow comes from the arrows used in battle.")
